Backport of upstream branch many/fix-tomodachi (commit 3e54fb4c33e1, 2026-04-28)
adapted for Eden v0.2.0-rc2 source layout.

Fixes SIGABRT/__stack_chk_fail in Tomodachi Life: Living the Dream when the
Vulkan compute pipeline configures more than `max_elements` image views in one
call. The previous static_vector overflows its fixed stack capacity; switching
to small_vector keeps the same inline capacity but spills the overflow to the
heap, avoiding the stack canary trip.

rc2 already pinned `max_elements = 64`, so the size argument is unchanged here;
upstream's master had it at 128 and reduced to 64 in the same commit.

--- a/src/video_core/renderer_vulkan/vk_compute_pipeline.cpp
+++ b/src/video_core/renderer_vulkan/vk_compute_pipeline.cpp
@@ -128,8 +128,8 @@ void ComputePipeline::Configure(Tegra::Engines::KeplerCompute& kepler_compute,
     texture_cache.SynchronizeComputeDescriptors();

     static constexpr size_t max_elements = 64;
-    boost::container::static_vector<VideoCommon::ImageViewInOut, max_elements> views;
-    boost::container::static_vector<VideoCommon::SamplerId, max_elements> samplers;
+    boost::container::small_vector<VideoCommon::ImageViewInOut, max_elements> views;
+    boost::container::small_vector<VideoCommon::SamplerId, max_elements> samplers;

     const auto& qmd{kepler_compute.launch_description};
     const auto& cbufs{qmd.const_buffer_config};
